  <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-3xl">
    <h1>About catchment.school</h1>

    <p>
      catchment.school is a free tool that helps parents and carers in England find schools in their local area,
      understand catchment area boundaries, and navigate the school admissions process.
    </p>

    <h2>What is a school catchment area?</h2>
    <p>
      A catchment area is the geographic zone from which a school gives priority to applications. If you live
      within a school's catchment area, your child is more likely to be offered a place — though this is not
      guaranteed, particularly for oversubscribed schools.
    </p>
    <p>
      Catchment areas are set by local authorities and individual schools. They can change each year depending
      on the number of applications received. The boundaries are published annually in each school's admissions
      policy.
    </p>

    <h2>How are catchment areas determined?</h2>
    <p>
      Most catchment areas in England are defined by a <strong>straight-line distance</strong> from the child's
      home address to the school. Some use a <strong>road-walking distance</strong>, and others use fixed
      geographic boundaries.
    </p>
    <p>
      The "last distance offered" in any given year tells you how far the furthest successful applicant lived
      from the school. This is published in most local authority admissions outcome data.
    </p>

    <h2>How to use this site</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Search by postcode</strong> — find schools within 5km of your home address</li>
      <li><strong>Browse by town or council</strong> — see all schools in your area</li>
      <li><strong>View school profiles</strong> — capacity, pupil numbers, age range and admissions policy type</li>
      <li><strong>Find official catchment documents</strong> — each school page links to the council's admissions portal</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Where does the data come from?</h2>
    <p>
      School data is sourced from the <a href="https://get-information-about-schools.service.gov.uk" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">
      Get Information About Schools (GIAS)</a> service, maintained by the Department for Education.
      This includes all open state-funded and independent schools in England.
    </p>
    <p>
      We update the dataset regularly to reflect school openings, closures and changes published by the DfE.
    </p>

    <h2>Important notice</h2>
    <p>
      Catchment area boundaries change annually. Always verify your address falls within a school's catchment
      by checking the school's official admissions policy or contacting your local authority directly before
      making any applications.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>
